HEADWORD: Jaunce
<hw>Jaunce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>jancer</ets>. Cf. <er>Jounce</er>, <er>Jaunt</er>.]</ety> <def>To
ride hard; to jounce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Spurr'd, galled and tired by <qex>jauncing</qex> Bolingbroke.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jaundice</ent>⟦br⟧
